OL,3,CWhy Starmer may fight on despite
OL,4,CLabour's worst election predictions
OL,6,FEarlier this year, one senior Labour
OL,7,Ffigure suggested to me that the prime
OL,8,Fminister was unlikely to be removed
OL,9,Faround a 'calendar event' because his
OL,10,Fadvisers would have time to prepare to
OL,11,Fdefend against any leadership
OL,12,Fchallenge.
OL,14,FNumber 10 has already pushed back
OL,15,Fparliament's return until Wednesday,
OL,16,Frestricting rebel MPs ability to meet
OL,17,Fup and plot, and the prime minister
OL,18,Fhas planned a speech for Monday
OL,19,Fmorning in a pre-emptive attempt to
OL,20,Freset any post-election narrative.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
